getAddress(string).details: Get address for a username (username is normalized to lowercase).      Returns address(0) if username doesn't exist.       FIX: Explicitly ensure we never return the contract's own address,      which would indicate a bug. Always return address(0) for non-existent usernames.

getUsername(address).details: Get username for an address (already stored normalized).

isValidUsername(string).details: Check if username is valid (alphanumeric and underscores only).

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

registerUsername(string).details: Register a username (regular).      If registrationFee > 0, collects fee in USDC.

registerUsernameForAddress(string,addres.details: Register username for a specific address (for factorycreated wallets).      feePayer can be the wallet itself or a relayer.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

transferUsername(address).details: Transfer username to another address.      Useful for selling/transferring handles.

updateUsername(string).details: Update username (only if current username is not premium).
